From: =?UTF-8?q?S=C3=B6nke=20Holz?= <sholz8530@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 11:52:30 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Set "development" to "false"

FIXME: Remove this patch when updating to the next release.

Binutils 2.46 was accidentally packaged with this variable set to true,
which leads to build errors because this enables -Werror.

https://sourceware.org/pipermail/binutils/2026-May/149177.html
---
 bfd/development.sh | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/bfd/development.sh b/bfd/development.sh
index 4f3952062f86f8b8326f075cc22786f6a57c7015..95859b161dfab1f5820e51a5c31d77770d90bde6 100644
--- a/bfd/development.sh
+++ b/bfd/development.sh
@@ -16,7 +16,7 @@
 # along with this program.  If not, see <http://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.
 
 # Controls whether to enable development-mode features by default.
-development=true
+development=false
 
 # Indicate whether this is a release branch.
 experimental=false
